reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Unpack and pack quickly and without messing up clothing.
reviews.reviewText: Without packing cubes, unpacking and re-packing during a trip is time consuming and clothes get messed up and creased. I roll up tops in one, socks in one, underclothes in one and toiletries in a 4th. Then all the folded items go in the bottom of the case. Four of these fit perfectly in a carry-on, allow easy access to contents and folded items. There are half size ones available, which may work better for toiletries and sundries (camera, cables, occasional medications). Eagle creek cubes are well made and the mesh on one side makes it easy to see what each one holds. I started using them, now everyone else in my family does; so easy to keep everything organized.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Most useful size
reviews.reviewText: Decided to add 3 more pieces of this size to my set since they are getting harder and harder to find. We now have a total of 12 pieces of this size. We’ve color coded our packs. Mine is black my wife’s got blue and our daughter has red. A bit hard to find the reds nowadays tho that every so often she ends up taking from my sets.We have these old models and prefer them to the newer ones. Unfortunately they aren’t as widely available nowadays. Have multiple pcs of each size. Simply the most useful durable cubes ever. Bought my first batch more than 10 years ago and still using them until today. Have bought a piece of the different newer models but still like these ones more

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Back packing has never been easier!
reviews.reviewText: At first I was skeptical that I needed these, but after using them on a few trips, I can't imagine living without them. They are very high quality and durable. I use two in my Osprey Kestral 38 along with a shoe bag, toiletry case, a half cube dry/wet Eagle Creek bag. The frames around the bag help keep everything structured, and can be squished to fit everything in my pack. The zippers aren't YKK, but I cant notice any differences. These keep me super organized and so I know exactly where all my things are. Hopefully I'll never misplace my underwear or socks again, ha.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It seems stupid, but highly practical for freq travelers
reviews.reviewText: These simple, highly durable nylon pouches may seem like an excess purchase for those who are always on the move (and to be honest, they may be). However, they excel at their purpose - they help you organize your suitcase/duffel/carry-on without fail. Packing (and unpacking!) is so much easier with these. After using these with my duffel bag, I could simply never revert to the unorganized mess I used to travel with.
